[b]Candle Pressure & Response (JMA)[/b] breaks each candle down into bidirectional pressure, rejection, efficiency, and expansion metrics, smoothed with Jurik Moving Average for cleaner panel readability.

[b]What it does[/b]

Standard candle analysis looks at body vs. wick ratios. This indicator goes further — measuring where within the candle's range price closed (pressure), how much of the range was rejected (rejection), how efficiently price moved from open to close (efficiency), and how this bar's range compares to recent volatility (expansion). All four dimensions are output as JMA-smoothed series on a dedicated panel.

[b]Metrics[/b]

[list]
[*][b]Bidirectional pressure[/b] — Bull and bear pressure scores per candle, normalized against ATR
[*][b]Rejection[/b] — Upper and lower wick rejection as a fraction of total range
[*][b]Efficiency[/b] — Close-to-open travel relative to total high-low range
[*][b]Expansion[/b] — Current candle range vs. ATR-based average; flags abnormal range bars
[*][b]JMA smoothing[/b] — All series smoothed with configurable Jurik MA for noise reduction
[*][b]Threshold alerts[/b] — Visual markers on the panel when any metric exceeds its threshold
[/list]

